+//! **THREE-stage heterogeneous ExpandA recursion chain, WITH the matvec ARITHMETIC tail** — the
+//! C-P6 soundness wire from `ρ` all the way to the real `ŵ_i` that invNTT/UseHint consumes.
+//!
+//! ## Upgrade over `expanda_chain3`
+//!
+//! `expanda_chain3.rs` (commit 4f4001f) proved a **3-leg** binding whose Leg M stopped at the
+//! ExpandA *placement* core: rejection-sample → one-hot placement → A-bank → the placed `Â[0][0]`
+//! surfaced to OUTPUT publics. The matrix-vector *arithmetic* — the pointwise `Â∘ẑ` mults, the
+//! `ĉ∘(t̂1·2^d)` subtractive leg and the accumulate-reduce that turn `Â` into `ŵ_i` — was the
+//! DEFERRED "heavy tail". **This example ports that tail VERBATIM into Leg M**, so the stage now
+//! outputs the REAL `ŵ_i = Σ_j Â[i][j]∘ẑ[j] − ĉ∘(t̂1_i·2^d)` (the value the downstream
+//! invNTT/UseHint stages consume), coefficient-exact against the `mldsa_verify_ref.rs` matvec row.
+//!
+//! ## STEP 0 scope decision — port the tail IN-AIR (extend Leg M), NOT a 4th leg
+//!
+//! Either shape was allowed. I EXTEND Leg M's AIR (placement + arithmetic in ONE batch-STARK leg)
+//! rather than adding a 4th arithmetic leg tied by a 3rd cross-stage equality, because:
+//!   - **Faithfulness.** `docs/bench/plonky3-shield-air/expanda_matvec_air.rs` (the reference,
+//!     item (iii)) is ONE AIR: the placed bank feeds the mult b-input DIRECTLY via the "diagonal
+//!     read" (bank[k] == az.b), with `Â` never surfaced as a public. A 4th leg would invent a NEW
+//!     seam (`Â` as cross-leg publics) that does not exist in the reference; extending Leg M
+//!     reproduces the reference's exact bank→mult wire.
+//!   - **24 GB fit.** Each additional leg adds a WHOLE `verify_batch_circuit` (FRI folding, Merkle
+//!     caps, Poseidon2) to the recursion witness — a large FIXED cost that dominates trace width.
+//!     Extending Leg M reuses the existing 3rd in-circuit verify; only Leg M's own trace widens
+//!     (193 → 1137 cols, height UNCHANGED at 512), which is cheaper than a 4th FRI verifier.
+//!
+//! **Leg M — the ExpandA placement core + matvec arithmetic** (verbatim from
+//! `expanda_matvec_air.rs`, reduced to l=1/N=64, C=320 kept):
+//!   - *Candidate rows* (320): the VERBATIM rejection gadget (`t = b0+256·b1+65536·(b2&0x7F)`;
+//!     accept iff `t<q` via the sound lt-comparator `t − q + lt·2²⁴ = diff`, 24-bit range-checked),
+//!     the VERBATIM one-hot placement (`Σ sel = place`, `Σ k·sel = cnt·place`, `place = lt·act`,
+//!     `act = [cnt<N]`), the VERBATIM A-bank write-xor-thread threading. `pi_stream` (320 packs)
+//!     is bound to INPUT publics.
+//!   - *Coefficient rows* (64): the VERBATIM base-2¹² limb-carry mod-q multiply (`ntt_mul_air.rs`,
+//!     296 cols/gadget) for `Â[0][k]·ẑ[0][k]`, the `2^d` scale `t̂1s = 8192·t̂1[k] mod q` (ζ pinned
+//!     to 8192), the subtractive `psub = ĉ[k]·t̂1s mod q` (its b-input ==-bound to the t1s output —
+//!     the c∘t1 wire), and the VERBATIM accumulate-reduce `Σ P − PSUB + q = out + k·q` (in-field
+//!     partial sums, `k ∈ [0,8)` canonical reduction — `ntt_accumulate_air.rs`). The placed bank
+//!     feeds the mult b-input via the factored diagonal read; `ẑ/t̂1/ĉ` are INPUT publics and the
+//!     resulting `ŵ_i[0..64]` is the OUTPUT public.
+//!
+//! ## Scope (REDUCED-BUT-REAL, l=1, N=64, C=320 kept)
+//!   - **l = 1** ExpandA entry (column j=0, output row i=0, nonce [0,0]); one additive product.
+//!   - **N = 64** coefficients: `ŵ_i[0..64]` over the placed `Â[0][0][0..64]`. NTT-domain
+//!     arithmetic is pointwise, so the reduced 64-coeff row is the same arithmetic, count reduced.
+//!   - **C = 320** candidate budget KEPT — all 320 of Leg B's validated packs are tied.
+//! `Â` is REAL FIPS-204 ExpandA on real libcrux seed-5 ρ (first 64 coeffs, diff-tested). The
+//! statement inputs `ẑ/ĉ/t̂1` are representative canonical NTT-domain residues (< q) — the tail's
+//! job is the ARITHMETIC, not re-deriving `ẑ/ĉ/t̂1`, which come from their own stages/publics. The
+//! output `ŵ_i` diff-tests coefficient-exact against the `mldsa_verify_ref.rs` matvec row
+//! (`Σ Â∘ẑ − ĉ∘(t̂1·2^d)`) computed the reference way.
+//!
+//! ## Format decision (as in `expanda_crossleg`)
+//! Each leg is a **single-instance batch-STARK proof** (`prove_batch`): AIR eval / trace / prep /
+//! public layout / witness IDENTICAL to the shipped uni-stark air, only the harness differs.
+//! Field re-cast BabyBear → KoalaBear (AIRs are generic over `PrimeField64`). Leg M uses the
+//! DEFAULT `preprocessed_next_row_columns` (open all at zeta+zeta_next) — the batch-STARK
+//! recursion requires it; the eval reads only the current preprocessed row.
+//!
+//! ## Two cross-stage ties, one outer proof
+//!   - **Tie 1** (S↔B): `Leg-S squeeze-output publics[34+b] == Leg-B stream-input publics[b]`,
+//!     b ∈ 0..960 (the 960 squeeze bytes).
+//!   - **Tie 2** (B↔M): `Leg-B pi_stream-output publics[960+r] == Leg-M pi_stream-input
+//!     publics[r]`, r ∈ 0..320 (the 320 packed candidates).
+//! Both via `cb.sub` + `cb.assert_zero` (each public read once — a direct `connect` breaks the
+//! Public-table LogUp). All THREE proofs verified in ONE recursion circuit → ONE outer proof.
+//!
+//! ## Cases (all in one run)
+//!   1. HONEST   (S(0,0) ∘ B(0,0-stream) ∘ M(0,0-stream)+matvec, both ties) -> outer prove+verify OK.
+//!   2. NEG1 (pi_stream mismatch, PRIMARY): M built over the DIFFERENT nonce-[1,0] stream, so
+//!      Leg-B packs ≠ Leg-M packs -> Tie 2 fails -> REJECTS at prove (WitnessConflict).
+//!   3. NEG2 (S↔B still rejects): B and M both over nonce [1,0] (Tie 2 holds) but S over [0,0],
+//!      so Tie 1 fails -> REJECTS at prove.
+//!   4. NEG3 (matvec tamper): a placed-Â coefficient is tampered on its mult-read row so `ŵ_i` is
+//!      wrong -> Leg M's OWN batch proof REJECTS at native verify (the tail's AIR soundness). A
+//!      second variant tampers an accumulate partial-sum P[0].
+//!
+//! ## Real-leg faithfulness gates (host, before proving)
+//!   - Leg S squeeze bytes == `tiny_keccak` SHAKE128(ρ‖[j,i]) byte-for-byte (independent XOF).
+//!   - rejection-sampled `pi_stream` == FIPS-204 incremental ExpandA reference, coefficient-exact.
+//!   - Leg B packs == byte recomposition of the squeeze bytes.
+//!   - Leg M placed `Â[0][0][0..64]` == FIPS-204 ExpandA reference (first 64 coeffs), exact.
+//!   - Leg M `ŵ_i[0..64]` == the `mldsa_verify_ref.rs` matvec row `Σ Â∘ẑ − ĉ∘(t̂1·2^d)`, exact.
+//!   - ρ == REAL libcrux ML-DSA-87 seed-5 ρ, re-derived by libcrux's own keygen H() step.
+//!
+//! ```bash
+//! cargo run --release --example expanda_chain_matvec
+//! ```
+
+#[macro_use]
+mod common;
+use common::*;
+
+use core::borrow::Borrow;
+use p3_air::{Air, AirBuilder, BaseAir, WindowAccess};
+use p3_batch_stark::{BatchProof, ProverData, StarkInstance, prove_batch, verify_batch};
+use p3_circuit_prover::{AirVariant, RecomposePreprocessor, recompose_air_builders};
+use p3_field::PrimeField64;
+use p3_keccak::KeccakF;
+use p3_keccak_air::{
+    KeccakCols, NUM_KECCAK_COLS, NUM_ROUNDS, NUM_ROUNDS_MIN_1, RC, U64_LIMBS, generate_trace_rows,
+};
+use std::time::Instant;
+use tiny_keccak::{Hasher, Shake, Xof};
+
+fn main() {
+    init_logger();
+    kb::run();
+}
+
+mod kb {
+    use super::*;
+
+    // KoalaBear, D=4, W=16 Poseidon2 — the same field/hash plumbing as `crossleg_bind`.
+    define_field_module_types!(
+        p3_koala_bear::KoalaBear,
+        p3_koala_bear::Poseidon2KoalaBear<16>,
+        p3_koala_bear::default_koalabear_poseidon2_16,
+        Poseidon2Config::KOALA_BEAR_D4_W16,
+        p3_poseidon2_circuit_air::KoalaBearD4Width16,
+        4,
+        16,
+        8,
